# Arch Knowledge

This directory holds the local architecture knowledge support files for the
repository.

## Structure

- `raw/` imported or copied reference material
- `daily/` append-oriented captured knowledge
- `knowledge/` compiled local knowledge articles
- `arch-statement.md` local configuration and intent
- `compliance-profile.yaml` adapter and policy configuration

If the repository installs the optional creativity-first pilot profile, it also
uses:

- `deviations/` documented local deviations from the current normative architecture

## Commands

```sh
arch-knowledge flush
arch-knowledge compile
arch-knowledge lint
```

If the repository uses `deviations/`, each record should make the normative
baseline, the local choice, and any proposal back to central architecture
explicit.

## Adapter setup

Default bootstrap installs `scripts/arch-llm-adapter.py`.

Set:

```sh
export ARCH_LLM_ADAPTER="python3 scripts/arch-llm-adapter.py"
export ARCH_LLM_TOOL_CMD="llm -m gpt-4.1-mini"
```

Replace `ARCH_LLM_TOOL_CMD` with any command that:

- accepts prompt text on `stdin`
- returns plain text on `stdout`

Examples:

```sh
export ARCH_LLM_TOOL_CMD="llm -m gpt-4.1-mini"
export ARCH_LLM_TOOL_CMD="aichat"
export ARCH_LLM_TOOL_CMD="python3 scripts/my-company-llm-wrapper.py"
```
